README.md
     1Ôćĺ# Tock
     5Ôćĺ[Features](#features) ÔÇó [Quick Start](#quick-start) ÔÇó [Commands](#commands) ÔÇó
     6Ôćĺ[Configuration](#configuration) ÔÇó [Theme](#theme) ÔÇó [File Format](#file-format) ÔÇó [Shell](#shell-completion) ÔÇó [Inspiration](#inspiration) ÔÇó [License](#license)
     7Ôćĺ
     8Ôćĺ## Features
    12Ôćĺ**Tock** is a powerful time tracking tool for the command line. It saves activity logs as plaintext files and provides an interactive terminal UI for viewing your time.
    13Ôćĺ
    14ÔćĺFeatures include:
    15Ôćĺ
    16Ôćĺ- ­čôŁ **Simple plaintext format** - Activities stored in human-readable files
    17Ôćĺ- ­čôů **Notes & Tags** - Attach detailed notes and tags to activities
    18Ôćĺ- ­čÄĘ **Interactive TUI** - Beautiful terminal calendar view using Bubble Tea
    19Ôćĺ- ÔÜí **Fast & Lightweight** - Single binary, no dependencies
    20Ôćĺ- ­čöä **Compatible** - Reads/writes Bartib file format and TimeWarrior data files
    21Ôćĺ- ­čÄĘ **Customizable Themes** - Multiple color themes and custom color support
    22Ôćĺ- ­čôů **iCal Export** - Generate .ics files for calendar integration, or sync with system calendars (macOS only)
    23Ôćĺ
    24Ôćĺ<hr clear="right"/>
    25Ôćĺ
    26Ôćĺ## Quick Start
    28Ôćĺ### Installation
    30Ôćĺ#### Homebrew (macOS)
    41Ôćĺ#### Go Install
    47Ôćĺ#### Build from source
    53Ôćĺ#### Install Script (Linux & macOS)
    59Ôćĺ#### Download Binary
    63Ôćĺ### Basic Usage
   116Ôćĺ## Configuration
   118ÔćĺTock supports a flexible configuration system using YAML files and environment variables.
   119Ôćĺ
   120Ôćĺ**Priority Order:**
   121Ôćĺ
   122Ôćĺ1. Command-line flags
   123Ôćĺ2. Environment variables
   124Ôćĺ3. Configuration file (`~/.config/tock/tock.yaml` or `./tock.yaml`)
   125Ôćĺ4. Default values
   126Ôćĺ
   127Ôćĺ### Configuration File
   165Ôćĺ### Environment Variables
   179Ôćĺ### Storage Backends
   183Ôćĺ### 1. Flat File (Default)
   191Ôćĺ### 2. TimeWarrior
   209Ôćĺ### Calendar View
   238Ôćĺ## Theming
   240ÔćĺTock supports customizable color themes for the calendar view.
   241Ôćĺ
   242ÔćĺYou can configure the theme in `tock.yaml`:
   243Ôćĺ
   244Ôćĺ```yaml
   245Ôćĺtheme:
   246Ôćĺ  name: custom
   247Ôćĺ  primary: "#ff0000"
   248Ôćĺ```
   249Ôćĺ
   250ÔćĺOr use environment variables:
   251Ôćĺ
   252Ôćĺ### Theme Name
   262Ôćĺ### Auto-detection
   270Ôćĺ### Custom Colors
   283Ôćĺ### Example: Cyberpunk / Fuchsia Theme
   300Ôćĺ### Time Format
   316Ôćĺ#### 12-Hour Format Examples
   328Ôćĺ#### 24-Hour Format (Default)
   343Ôćĺ## Commands
   345Ôćĺ```bash
   346Ôćĺ
   347ÔćĺA simple timetracker for the command line
   348Ôćĺ
   349ÔćĺUsage:
   350Ôćĺ  tock [command]
   351Ôćĺ
   352ÔćĺAvailable Commands:
   353Ôćĺ  add         Add a completed activity
   354Ôćĺ  analyze     Analyze your productivity patterns
   355Ôćĺ  calendar    Show interactive calendar view
   356Ôćĺ  completion  Generate the autocompletion script for the specified shell
   357Ôćĺ  continue    Continues a previous activity
   358Ôćĺ  current     Lists all currently running activities
   359Ôćĺ  help        Help about any command
   360Ôćĺ  ical        Generate iCal (.ics) file for a specific task, all tasks in a day, or all tasks
   361Ôćĺ  last        List recent unique activities
   362Ôćĺ  list        List activities (Calendar View)
   363Ôćĺ  remove      Remove an activity
   364Ôćĺ  report      Generate time tracking report
   365Ôćĺ  start       Start a new activity
   366Ôćĺ  stop        Stop the current activity
   367Ôćĺ  version     Print the version info
   368Ôćĺ  watch       Display a full-screen stopwatch for the current activity
   369Ôćĺ
   370ÔćĺFlags:
   371Ôćĺ  -b, --backend string   Storage backend: 'file' (default) or 'timewarrior'
   372Ôćĺ      --config string    Config file directory (default is $HOME/.config/tock/tock.yaml)
   373Ôćĺ  -f, --file string      Path to the activity log file (or data directory for timewarrior)
   374Ôćĺ  -h, --help             help for tock
   375Ôćĺ  -v, --version          version for tock
   376ÔćĺUse "tock [command] --help" for more information about a command.
   377Ôćĺ```
   378Ôćĺ
   379Ôćĺ[**Ôćĺ Commands Reference**](docs/commands.md)
   380Ôćĺ
   381Ôćĺ### Start tracking
   401Ôćĺ### Stop tracking
   418Ôćĺ### Add past activity
   439Ôćĺ### Remove activity
   453Ôćĺ### Continue activity
   472Ôćĺ### Current activity
   482Ôćĺ### Stopwatch (Watch Mode)
   500Ôćĺ### Recent activities
   513Ôćĺ### Calendar View (TUI)
   528Ôćĺ### Text Report
   551Ôćĺ### Calendar Integration (iCal)
   578Ôćĺ### Productivity Analysis
   602Ôćĺ## Update Check
   604ÔćĺTock automatically checks for updates once a week. When a new version is available, you will see a notification after running commands like `start` or `stop`.
   605Ôćĺ
   606ÔćĺYou can disable this check by setting `check_updates: false` in your configuration file or using the environment variable `TOCK_CHECK_UPDATES=false`.
   607Ôćĺ
   608Ôćĺ## File Format
   610ÔćĺActivities are stored in plaintext format (compatible with Bartib):
   611Ôćĺ
   612Ôćĺ```
   613Ôćĺ  2025-12-10 09:00 - 2025-12-10 11:30 | Project Name | Task description
   614Ôćĺ  2025-12-10 13:00 | Another Project | Ongoing task
   615Ôćĺ```
   616Ôćĺ
   617ÔćĺYou can edit this file manually with any text editor.
   618Ôćĺ
   619Ôćĺ## Shell Completion
   621ÔćĺTock supports shell completion for Bash, Zsh, Fish, and PowerShell. This includes basic command completion and **intelligent suggestions** for:
   622Ôćĺ
   623Ôćĺ- **Projects**: Suggests existing project names when using `-p` / `--project`.
   624Ôćĺ- **Descriptions**: Suggests recent activity descriptions when using `-d` / `--description`.
   625Ôćĺ  - Suggestions are context-aware: if a project is selected, it only suggests descriptions previously used for that project.
   626Ôćĺ- **Continue IDs**: Suggests valid activity IDs (with details) for the `tock continue` command.
   627Ôćĺ
   628Ôćĺ### Installation
   656Ôćĺ## Shell Integration
   658ÔćĺYou can display the current tracked activity directly in your shell prompt.
   659Ôćĺ
   660Ôćĺ### Zsh / Oh My Zsh
   679Ôćĺ### Starship
   692Ôćĺ### Technology Stack
   698Ôćĺ### Project Structure
   709Ôćĺ## Inspiration
   711ÔćĺTock is inspired by and compatible with [Bartib](https://github.com/nikolassv/bartib) - an excellent time tracking tool written in Rust by Nikolas Schmidt-Voigt. It's saved me countless hours and helped me stay organized, so I wanted to create a similar tool in Go with a clean architecture approach and an interactive terminal UI.
   712Ôćĺ
   713Ôćĺ## License
   715ÔćĺGPL-3.0-or-later

